cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM

The paper focuses on automatic license plate detection and recognition using computer vision and image processing techniques, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for LP detection, segmentation, and recognition suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the challenges of LP recognition in different languages and fonts, which may suggest the sub-category of information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the use of multiple datasets and the evaluation of the proposed framework's robustness and efficiency may suggest the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM).
